<subSubSection id="C33311E1FFEE7F0799F7E784D25DF915" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFEE7F0799F7E784D5F7FAC9" blockId="43.[151,1436,1205,1727]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F0799F7E784D53CFABF" bold="true" box="[198,558,1275,1301]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
Locally common in mountains of 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F079AEFE783D37AFABC" box="[990,1128,1276,1302]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F079D4BE783D21CFABC" box="[1146,1294,1276,1302]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F079C10E783D28AFABC" box="[1313,1432,1276,1302]" name="Colombia" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F0799A6E65DD604FA96" box="[151,278,1314,1340]" name="Venezuela" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F079812E65DD69BFA96" box="[291,393,1314,1340]" name="Ecuador" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F0798A7E65DD6C2FA96" box="[406,464,1314,1340]" name="Peru" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F079B23E65DD57DFA96" box="[530,623,1314,1340]" name="Bolivia" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. Found in open habitats in humid montane forests, along roads, on landslides, and near streams, (800–) 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFEE7F079B0BE636D5F3FAC9" box="[570,737,1353,1379]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.325" metricValueMax="3.25" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="m" value="2325.0" valueMax="3250.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–3250 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFEE7F0799F7E610D25DF915" blockId="43.[151,1436,1205,1727]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F0799F7E610D621FA23" bold="true" box="[198,307,1391,1417]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEE7F079802E60FD520FA23" authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Mett." box="[307,562,1392,1417]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F079802E60FD520FA23" box="[307,562,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Sticherus rubiginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group of five closely related species, which also includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEE7F079CB7E60FD7ECFA1A" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Gleichenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brittonii">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F079CB7E60FD7ECFA1A" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">S. brittonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEE7F079821E6E8D6DCFA1A" authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Christ" box="[272,462,1431,1456]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strictissimus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F079821E6E8D6DCFA1A" box="[272,462,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">S. strictissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEE7F0798D1E6E8D567FA1A" authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[480,629,1431,1456]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="farinosus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F0798D1E6E8D567FA1A" box="[480,629,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">S. farinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEE7F079B8CE6E8D476FA1A" authorityName="Lellinger" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Maxon &amp; C. V. Morton" box="[701,868,1431,1456]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Gleichenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F079B8CE6E8D476FA1A" box="[701,868,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">S. boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All five species have been considered to be conspecific (e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFEE7F0798BAE6C2D596FA7D" author="Tryon, R. M. &amp; Stolze, R. G." box="[395,644,1469,1495]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref34267" refString="Tryon, R. M. &amp; Stolze, R. G. (1989) Pteridophyta of Peru. Part II. 13. Pteridaceae - 15. Dennstaedtiaceae. Fieldiana Botany, n. s. 22: 1 - 122." type="book chapter" year="1989">Tryon &amp; Stolze 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFEE7F079BA1E6C2D4F0FA7D" author="Ostergaard A. &amp; Ollgaard, E." box="[656,994,1469,1495]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="107 - 169" refId="ref33047" refString="Ostergaard A., Ollgaard, E. &amp; B. (2001) Gleicheniaceae. In Harling, G. &amp; Andersson, L. (eds.), Flora of Ecuador 66: 107 - 169." type="journal article" year="2001">Østergaard &amp; Øllgaard 2001</bibRefCitation>
). They all have lanceolate branch and bud scales with a marginal to central pattern of scale darkening, but they differ in the degree of separation of the segments, the shape of the midvein scales, the prominence of the veinlets, and to some degree, in the pattern of scale darkening. Most collections from the complex surrounding 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEE7F079D09E54ED3F4F9E0" authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Mett." box="[1080,1254,1585,1610]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEE7F079D09E54ED3F4F9E0" box="[1080,1254,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">S. rubiginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can readily be placed into the five species we propose. However, there are some specimens, especially from 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEE7F079DD1E527D22BF9D8" box="[1248,1337,1624,1650]" name="Bolivia" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, that are either intermediate between species or show a unique combination of characters. Since these specimens do not form a uniform group or show an indication of hybridity, they cannot be delimited as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
